article.headline: Youngstown State 68, Cleveland St. 63
article.story: CLEVELAND (AP) -- Quin Humphrey scored 27 points and Mike Adams hit two clinching free throws with 7 seconds left to give Youngstown State a 68-63 victory over Cleveland State on Saturday night. Adams' dunk with 8:40 left gave the Penguins (7-12, 4-5 Horizon League) the lead for good at 53-51. Adams then hit a free throw before Keston Roberts, who scored 16 points, made two free throws and Adams a jumper to make it 58-51 with 5:25 remaining. The teams traded baskets until Carlos English hit a 3-pointer with 1:41 left to cut Youngstown State's lead to 66-63. With neither team scoring, Cleveland State then missed three 3-pointers and three shots inside the arc before Adams rebounded a missed 3 by English with 9 seconds left. Adams, who finished with nine points and eight rebounds, hit both shots to close the scoring. Ije Nwankwo led Cleveland State (8-11, 4-5) with 13 points, Raheem Moss adding 12 and J'nathan Bullock 10.
